													<tr><td valign="top" width="100%">&nbsp;<br>
													<!-- strMainData goes here-->
													<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='header' bgcolor='black' width='100%'>PALADIN STRATEGIES AND PLAYGUIDES</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='spti'>STATS FOR THE PALADIN CLASS</font> - <small>Tiberious Valtorus, Fennin Ro</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'> I wanted to start out saying when playing a Paladin in general the stats you will need to make this class more effective in the 
role of a tank are as follows.<P>
Many players play high elf for there wisdom but you are not a cleric you are 3/4 fighter 1/4 cleric. So go with stats that will help you more so Wis is needed but not so much it doesnt make that big a difference.
Best stats for Paladin in general:<P>

Str: high as you can helps your attack and you will do more damage when you get passed 20nth level.
Example: 150 str Soulfire 23 base damage, max damage hit for (96).<P>

Dex: Proccing of weapons when you get them makes a huge difference compared to those with low dex.<P>

Stamina: Helps you in long battles and somewhat on HP but not as much a big deal. (helps for swimming also)<P>

Agility: 75 Base is well good enough doesnt make that big a difference.<P>

Int: I play a Dwarf my Int is 60 thrill and now at 49 Im glad its not high my skills raise quite fast at my level and most skills are already capped,
Dont waste the time on int you will feel it when your 50th when you could have had higher str or what not instead.<P>

Wis: I have found 90 wis will give you 5 greater Heals at level 48, nice for after a fight but when a mob is hitting someone for 100s at a time you are wasting your time here,
Its better to use what mana you have for rooting or stunning a monster then healing somone who is going to die anyways.<P>

Greater heals help somewhat but in fights where you get spanked for 100 90s in damage taunt and use root more often then a heal spell.
On Races its for you to decide if you want the best race for the class then a Dwarf is the way to go!<P>

Dwarfs start out with what you need the most:<P>

100 str I put 10 here <br>
90 dex<br>
95 stamina and 5 here<br>
70 agil  put 5 points in here <br>
88 wis<br>
60 int thrill<br>
55 chr no big deal<br>
<P>
Later as you level you will see if you want to raise your int some to speed up learning 
you can buy jewelry but its really not nessacarry.<br><br>
I play a Troll warrior whos dumb as a rock 55 int and his skill gain fast 
Int is over rated.<br><br>
Ah well enough of my babbling,<br><br>

Tiberious Valtorus<br>
49nth Paladin Fennin ro.

		</td></tr>
